[{"id":"VR816498","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of a curve in a gridded plane. The horizontal axis is labeled volume, and the vertical axis is labeled pressure. The curve starts at point A with coordinates 1 comma 4 and moves downward and to the right, steeply at first and then more gradually, to point B with coordinates 4 comma 1.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR816498.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An ideal gas is sealed in a container with a moveable piston and is taken through the isothermal process from State <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> to State <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P V\"><math alttext=\"P V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>PV</mi></math></span></span> diagram. Which of the following correctly indicates whether the work done on the gas is positive or negative during the process, and provides a valid justification?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR816498_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Negative, because the gas expands</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Negative, because the pressure decreases</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Positive, because the gas expands</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Positive, because the pressure decreases</p>"],"answer":0}]